OL,6,FThe Medical Specialist Group
OL,7,Fpreviously confirmed that Dr Shokouh-
OL,8,FAmiri worked for them from 31 October
OL,9,F2016 to 31 August 2019 when he left
OL,10,Fthe partnership and he has not seen
OL,11,Fpatients in Guernsey since January
OL,12,F2019.
OL,14,FIn a written judgment, the Tribunal
OL,15,Fexplained: "Dr Shokouh-Amiri's
OL,16,Fmisconduct was serious and had the
OL,17,Fpotential to affect the public's
OL,18,Fconfidence in the profession.
